									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/sarahviren/">Sarah Viren</a></h6>
										Sarah Viren is a contributing writer for the <em>New York Times Magazine</em> and author of the essay collection <em>Mine</em>, which was a finalist for a Lambda Literary Award and longlisted for the PEN/Diamonstein-Spielvogel Award for the <em>Art of the Essay</em>, and the memoir <em>To Name the Bigger Lie</em>, a <em>New York Times</em> Editor’s Choice and named a best book of the year by <em>NPR</em> and <em>LitHub</em> in 2023. A National Endowment for the Arts Fellow and a National Magazine Award finalist, Viren teaches in the creative writing program at Arizona State University.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="https://sarahviren.com/" target="_blank" class="external">https://sarahviren.com/</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div>
													<div class="sidebar_content ad_bottom">
								<li id="custom_ads-24" class="widget Custom_Ads"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_F"></div></li>
							</div>
